               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl550-1">J.-B. Chabot, De sancti Isaaci Ninivite vita, scriptis et doctrina (Paris, 1892). BHO, 540-41. Liber castitatis, n° 125. A.J. Wensinck, Mystic Treatises by Isaac of Ninive (Amsterdam, 1927). S. Chiala, Dall'ascesi eremitica alla misericordia infinita. Ricerche su Isacco di Ninive e la sua fortuna (Firenze, 2002). BSO, II, 245- 46 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Isaac was the bishop of Ninevah.  He was originally from Beth Qatraye.  He went to Huzistan and to the mountain of Mattut where he established the monastery of Rabban Shapur, where he was buried.  </note>
